Note:
Runa Standard Library: Data Compression Utilities

Provides comprehensive data compression utilities including multiple compression algorithms, archive handling, and advanced compression features.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
  Let compressed be compress data with algorithm as "gzip"
  Let archive be create archive with files as file_list
  Let extracted be extract archive to directory "output"
  Let compressed_file be compress file "input.txt" to "output.gz"

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
  Let result be compress with data as input_data and algorithm as compression_algorithm
  Let result be create with files as file_list and format as archive_format
:End Note

Process called "compress_data" that takes data as String and algorithm as String returns List[Integer]:
    Return compress_data_with_algorithm(data, algorithm)

